THE TROUBLESHOOTING LADDER
══════════════════════════

    When debugging network issues, work through the layers:

         ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
    7    │  APPLICATION   HTTP 404? API timeout?       │  ← curl, wget
         ├─────────────────────────────────────────────┤
    4    │  TRANSPORT     Connection refused? Timeout? │  ← nc, ss
         ├─────────────────────────────────────────────┤
    3    │  NETWORK       Can't ping? No route?        │  ← ping, traceroute
         ├─────────────────────────────────────────────┤
    2    │  DATA LINK     ARP issues? MAC problems?    │  ← arp, ip neigh
         └─────────────────────────────────────────────┘

    Start from the bottom. Work up. Each layer depends on the ones below.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

MODULE MISSIONS
═══════════════

    [1] conn-diagnosis   Systematically Diagnose Connection Failures
    [2] packet-capture   Capture Network Packets with tcpdump
    [3] path-trace       Trace Network Routes

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

SKILLS YOU WILL LEARN
═════════════════════

    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
    │  COMMAND          │  PURPOSE                                       │
    ├───────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
    │  nc -zv           │  Test if ports are open                        │
    │  tcpdump          │  Capture and analyze packets                   │
    │  traceroute       │  Trace path to destination                     │
    │  mtr              │  Combined ping + traceroute                    │
    │  ss               │  Show socket statistics                        │
    │  curl -v          │  Verbose HTTP debugging                        │
    └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

